data.text:
Adelaidea (3 February 1496 - 23 May 1534) was sovereign Grand Countess of Ghent and Countess of Horten by marriage. She was the second daughter of Philip I of Castile and Isabella of Genovia and twin of Elizabeth of Austria, Archduchess of Genovia.

Early Life[]

Adelaide was born in Bruges of 3 February 1496 alongside her sister Elizabeth of Austria. Their mother, Isabella, was pregnant with Adelaide and Elizabeth when she gave birth to Adelaide's sister Isabelle of Austria. Isabelle, Adelaide and Elizabeth were originally meant to be triplets. She was named Adelaide after Adelaidea of Hungary, Queen of Genovia.
